table row some shortcuts -

*NOTE :- Todays more get challeges for convert tabular structure data to mobile devices.
       - Human brain are trained to view table from LEFT to RIGHT.

tr = table row
th = table heading
td = table data

Shortcuts - Create table with heading --> table>tr>th*3

E.g. -	But Output is not table perfect 
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Country</th>
            <th>Country CODE</th>
            <th>Email</th>
        </tr>
    </table>


*NOTE :- Editors made minimize your code written practice & bugs.

Shortcuts - Create table data -->tr>td*3

E.g. - 
    <tr>
        <td>India</td>
        <td>In</td>
        <td>india@google.com</td>
    </tr>
	

Shortcuts - multiple copies any code --> alt+shift+down arrow

E.g. - Table output can do better using CSS


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
      <meta charset="UTF-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
      <title>Table</title>
      <style>
            table {
                  width: 100%;
                  border-collapse: collapse; <!-- table have self border  -->
                  text-align: center;
            }

            td, th {
                  border: 1px solid black;
                  padding: 10px;
            }

            tr:nth-child(even) {
                  background-color: #c9c9c9;
            }


      </style>
</head>
<body>
      <table>
            <tr>
                  <th>Country</th>
                  <th>Country CODE</th>
                  <th>Email</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                  <td>India</td>
                  <td>In</td>
                  <td>india@google.com</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                  <td>United States of America</td>
                  <td>USA</td>
                  <td>usa@google.com</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                  <td>Japan</td>
                  <td>JP</td>
                  <td>jp@google.com</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                  <td>China</td>
                  <td>CN</td>
                  <td>cn@google.com</td>
            </tr>
            
      </table>
</body>
</html>



*NOTE :- Under Border actually table part majorly enhance through CSS.

cell   ==> India
row    ==> Horizontal all LEFT to RIGHT i.e. India.. to.. india@google.com
column ==> Vertical TOP to BOTTOM i.e. Country.. to.. China


Top to bottom heading code - 

E.g. -

<table>
            <tr>
                  <th>Country</th>
                  <td>India</td>
                  <td>Japan</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                  <th>CODE</th>
                  <td>IN</td>
                  <td>JP</td>
            </tr>
      </table>




Detail adjustment of column - colspan 

E.g. - colspan gives any space than other

<table>
            <tr>
                  <th colspan="3">Country</th>
                  <td>India</td>
                  <td>Japan</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                  <th>CODE</th>
                  <td>IN</td>
                  <td>JP</td>
            </tr>
      </table>


Detail adjustment of row - rowspan 

